		<div class="collapse" id="procedure" style="height: 0px;">
			<ol>
				<li>
					Make connections of power supply, capacitor, inductor, transistor and load resistor to build the buck converter.
					<br>Vin = 12; D = 0.4; C = 2000e-6; L = 150e-6; R = 50; RL = 0.1; Rc = 0.1;
				</li>
				<li>Check the circuit connections according to the schematics.</li>
				<li>
					Varying duty cycle
					<ol type="I">
						<li>Set the duty cycle at 40%, and switching frequency at 20 kHz.</li>
						<li>Observe and measure the output voltage.</li>
						<li>Vary the duty cycle from 20% to 80% with the interval of 10%.</li>
						<li>Measure the output voltage for each of the duty cycle. Compare the measurement with theoretical calculation.</li>
					</ol>
				</li>
				<li>
					Varying switching frequency
					<ol type="I">
						<li>Set the duty cycle at 40%, and switching frequency at 20 kHz.</li>
						<li>Observe and measure the output voltage ripple. Compare the measurement with theoretical calculation.</li>
						<li>
							Increase the switching frequency to 50 kHz. Observe and measure the output voltage ripple. Compare
							the measurement with theoretical calculation.
						</li>
						<li>
							Decrease the switching frequency to 10 kHz. Observe and measure the output voltage ripple. Compare
							the measurement with theoretical calculation.
						</li>
					</ol>
				</li>
				<li>
					Varying load resistor
					<ol type="I">
						<li>Set the duty cycle at 40%, and switching frequency at 20 kHz.</li>
						<li>Measure the load current and output voltage when the load resistance is 20 Ω.</li>
						<li>Measure the load current and output voltage when the load resistance is 10 Ω.</li>
					</ol>
				</li>
				<li>
					Closed loop voltage control
					<ol type="I">
						<li>Connect the references as shown in the figure.</li>
						<li>
							Enter the value of the desired output voltage ranging from 20-40V in the intervals of 5V, the controller
							will compare the output voltage and the reference value and adjust the duty cycle accordingly.
						</li>
					</ol>
				</li>
